data.name: groupBox1.ToolTip
data.value: Change gamma value with the slider. gamma value > 1 ---> Darkness. gamma value < 1 ---> brightness. The slider have values (0.1-5). Hint: it is prefered to use this technique as the last one becuase the change does not effect on other processes.

data.name: button8.ToolTip
data.value: Using Laplacian of Gaussian operator , Note: Edge detection is sensitive to spark noise so, you need to remove it by using smoothing filter first before detecting edges. (sharpening) ----------------------------------------------------------- There is always an edge between two adjacent regions with differentgrayscale values. We can make use of it to define a boundary of the object

data.name: label11.ToolTip
data.value: Used to divide the image into two regions (object and background), we define a single threshold value. Which known as the global threshold. Hint: move the slider to adjust the TH value, then click adjust to save it.

data.name: button31.ToolTip
data.value: Sobel filter ---> find edge by finding sharp changes in intensities, it sensitive to the noise (increase spark noise), So usually it needs a smooth filter before detecting edges. Hint: This button detect edge horizontally ( in X direction)

data.name: button22.ToolTip
data.value: Sobel filter ---> find edge by finding sharp changes in intensities, it sensitive to the noise (increase spark noise), So usually it needs a smooth filter before detecting edges. Hint: This button detect edge Vertically ( in Y direction)
